article.headline: ETSU 73, Dayton 68
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Justin Tubbs scored 26 points to lead East Tennessee State on a second-half surge to hold off Dayton 73-68 on Wednesday night. The Buccaneers (3-2) trailed 38-33 at the break, but began the second half on an 18-2 run to take a 51-40 lead with 13:50 left in the game. The Flyers (5-2) shot 10 for 36 after halftime (27.8 percent) en route to their second consecutive loss after starting 5-0. Dayton's overall shooting percentage of 33.3 percent (22 for 66) was a vast improvement over the 20 percent shooting effort (12 of 60) the Flyers posted in a 68-34 blowout loss to Cincinnati on Nov. 27. ETSU shot 12 for 22 from the floor (54.5 percent) in the second and led by as many 64-55 with 1:35 to play. Chris Wright grabbed 15 rebounds and scored 13 points for Dayton. Mike Smith scored 17 points and Micah Williams added 16 for the Buccaneers.
